### How to Modify It

To add a new dependency to a field in your test, update the `ProcessingOrder` slice for that field in the test function. For example, in `TestDetermineProcessingOrder_WithDependencies` (lines 34–77), if you want the `"address"` field to also depend on `"country"`, modify the `ProcessingOrder` value:

```go
// Before (lines 44–48)
{
    Key: "address",
    Definition: &jsonSchema.Definition{
        Type:            jsonSchema.String,
        ProcessingOrder: []string{"city", "country"},
    },
},
```

To add a new dependency (e.g., `"zipcode"`), change it to:

```go
// After
{
    Key: "address",
    Definition: &jsonSchema.Definition{
        Type:            jsonSchema.String,
        ProcessingOrder: []string{"city", "country", "zipcode"},
    },
},
```

Make sure `"zipcode"` is also defined as a field in the `fields` slice. For example, add:

```go
{
    Key: "zipcode",
    Definition: &jsonSchema.Definition{Type: jsonSchema.String},
},
```

This change ensures that the `"address"` task will depend on `"city"`, `"country"`, and `"zipcode"` when the processing order is determined. Always verify that the new dependency key exists in the `fields` slice to avoid it being ignored by the analyzer.

