The `JobSubmitterFactory` function is typically integrated into systems that require dynamic job submission strategies, such as distributed message queue consumers or scalable microservices architectures. Below is an example of how it fits into a Kafka-based job processing pipeline with dependency injection and resource management:

```go
// Go

// Dependency injection setup
type SubmitterProvider struct {
