}

// Goroutine pool for high-performance processing
pool := workerpool.New(10) // limit concurrency

provider := NewSubmitterProvider(config.SubmitterType)
consumer := kafka.NewConsumer(config.KafkaConfig)

for msg := range consumer.Messages() {
    m := msg // capture loop variable
    pool.Submit(func() {
        handleKafkaMessage(m, provider)
    })
}
```

In this architecture, `JobSubmitterFactory` enables the system to select the appropriate job submitter implementation at runtime, supporting flexible deployment scenarios. The factory is injected into consumers, which process messages from Kafka using a goroutine pool for efficient resource utilization. This pattern ensures that job submission logic is decoupled from message handling and can be easily extended or swapped based on operational requirements.

