### How to Modify It

To change the implementation of the `Process` method in the `ClientAdapter` interface, you need to update the code where this interface is implemented. For example, if you want to add logging before processing the inputs, locate the file where your struct implements `ClientAdapter` (e.g., `client.go`). Find the method with the signature:

```go
func (c *YourClientStruct) Process(inputs *llmManagement.Inputs) (*openai.ChatCompletionResponse, error) {
    // existing code
}
```

Add your logging statement at the beginning of this method:

```go
func (c *YourClientStruct) Process(inputs *llmManagement.Inputs) (*openai.ChatCompletionResponse, error) {
    fmt.Println("Processing inputs:", inputs) // Add this line
    // existing code
}
```

Make sure to import `"fmt"` at the top of your file if it’s not already present. This change will log the inputs every time `Process` is called. Only the implementation file needs to be modified; the interface definition in `clientManager/clientManager.go` remains unchanged.

