This pattern enables high-performance, scalable processing by decoupling the conversion logic from the message handling. The converter can be swapped for testing or extended for other response formats. Resource management is handled by ensuring HTTP response bodies are closed promptly, preventing leaks in long-running services. This approach fits well in cloud-native environments, supporting maintainability and extensibility.
